    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES70-5 - REASSEMBLY -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a lubricated needle bearing in 1st speed gear. Install 1st speed gear and a thrust
                washer on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301139">Figure 39</hotlnk>). The clutching teeth should face the output end of the
                mainshaft. Secure with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301139" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301139" filename="../figg13/g1301139.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. 1st Speed Gear and Thrust Washer On Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to prevent possible personal injury from flying pieces of metal when
                        pressing components onto a shaft.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place Moly #2 lubricant on the shaft, then install the two-piece caged needle bearing and
                thrust washer onto the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301140">Figure 40</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301140" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301140" filename="../figg13/g1301140.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Install Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the 2nd speed gear on the shaft. The clutching teeth should face up toward the input
                end of the shaft. Install the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear and secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301141">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301141" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301141" filename="../figg13/g1301141.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. 2nd Speed Gear On Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the fluted shaft diameters with Moly #2 lubricant. Then install the 2nd-3rd speed
                synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301142">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301142" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301142" filename="../figg13/g1301142.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Install 2nd - 3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place Moly #2 lubricant on the shaft fluted diameters. Then install 3rd speed gear (clutch
                teeth down) and thrust washer on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301143">Figure 43</hotlnk>). Secure them with a snap ring. Place the pin in the spacer
                sleeve. Hold it in place with a dab of grease. Then use a driver to install the spacer sleeve.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301143" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301143" filename="../figg13/g1301143.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. 3rd Speed Gear and Thrust Washer On Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable driver to install 4th speed gear onto the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301144">Figure 44</hotlnk>). The clutch teeth should face up toward the input side of
                the shaft. Secure with a washer and snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301144" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301144" filename="../figg13/g1301144.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. 4th Speed Gear Onto Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place 4th-5th speed synchronizer on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301145">Figure 45</hotlnk>). Use a suitable driver to install the pocket bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301145" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301145" filename="../figg13/g1301145.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. 4th-5th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the mainshaft on the bench. Install 1st-reverse clutch gear, lubricated caged needle
                bearing, and reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301146">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301146" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301146" filename="../figg13/g1301146.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Install 1st - Reverse Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable driver to install the output bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301147">Figure 47</hotlnk>). This bearing must be firmly seated against the thrust
                washer to prevent the washer from moving.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301147" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301147" filename="../figg13/g1301147.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Install Output Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
